The paper discusses the Shannon channel capacity equation and proposes a method to break through the Shannon Limit in digital communication. This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also analyzes the signal uncertainty principle, which is related to Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the physical theoretical basis of the Shannon theory, which is related to Physics (cs.PHY).
